Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.04,0:00:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.02,0:00:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.39,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:42.98,Default,,0,0,30,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.98,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,30,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:59.24,Default,,0,0,30,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.24,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,30,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.55,Default,,0,0,30,,Men, don't you ever let others see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.17,0:01:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Air raid! Air raid!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.01,0:01:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Start up! Start me up! {same as in prev. ep}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.04,0:02:13.28,Sign,,0,0,250,,{\b1\blur1\fs50\bord0\c&HF1F4F8&}Episode 15 \N{\fs110}Rabaul Air Corps
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.28,0:02:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,First observation post reported 50 aircraft passing by. {/over/above them}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.82,0:02:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus 30 planes in a new formation. \NContinuing the observation. {no clue what he means by "new formation (e.g. of aircraft) - 30 planes, continuing/following goal" - maybe he means "new model" or idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.59,0:02:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's over a 100 planes... {no clue where did he get this from, as well as what the previous lines meant, 100機は越すな ; maybe that "formation" meant "pairs of planes" or something that'd bring the total to 110?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it. Their numbers are growing by the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.35,0:02:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What about our planes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.70,0:02:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir. Already at less than half strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.52,0:02:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.86,0:02:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,After the withdrawal from Guadalcanal Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.95,0:02:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the Rabaul Base on New Britain Island
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.37,0:02:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,served as a front line base, \Nprotecting the southern resources in Japanese hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.91,0:02:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But by the summer of 1943,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.23,0:03:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the US Army had wrestled the mastery of sea and air \Nin the Rabaul area out of Japanese hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.25,0:03:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Chiefly, the US military aimed \Nto stop any resupply from the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.02,0:03:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, they planned to destroy the Tokyo Express. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tokyo_Express}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.57,0:04:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Its sheer size allowed the US Army \Nto switch to offensive operations. {actually "counteroffensive" but I think by 1943 it's already offensive rather than counter}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.07,0:04:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Rabaul Base was the primary fulcrum \Nof Japan's Southern Strategy,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.28,0:04:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which is why air raids against it \Nwere being launched daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.10,0:04:37.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H131B1E&\3c&H8B8D94&}The 26th Air Squadron Command{ Headquarters} {believing HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.34,0:04:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.03,0:04:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the Combined Fleet Headquarters still idle? {lit: still don't move}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.43,0:04:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, it seems reinforcing Rabaul \Nis not among their priorities. {lit: they don't think about reinforcing rabaul}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The Rabaul Air Corps will have to make do \Nwith what they currently have.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.83,0:04:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got cold feet! {no clue what he says, was "It's over optimistic." in HA; judging by next line, this gotta be something offensive}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.94,0:04:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Wing commander! {no clue, -jou gotta be some military rank/commander but I can't make out which one; could as well be his name, but they don't normally just address people by name without a military rank or at least a honorifics; will be used again at 5:13 but still no clue - I'm at a complete loss, I suggest just shove in whatever obscure aviation rank, Paul}\NYou don't have to go that far. {lit: words too much - basically just "watch your mouth"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.44,0:04:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But Wing Commander, {飛行長 is not a real japanese word, consists of words "aviation" and "commander", not technically the same as kamijou}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.21,0:05:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the recon aircraft reports \Nthat here in New Guinea,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.21,0:05:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,between Lae, Port Moresby, and the Guadalcanal Island, \Nthe enemy had amassed over a 100 planes on their airfields!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.40,0:05:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious they're poised for an attack! {lit: I can understand their offensive capability has been strengthened}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.25,0:05:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think we should leave them be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.10,0:05:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wing Commander! {this kamijou again, no clue what's dane}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.79,0:05:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.35,0:05:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Aviation Staff Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.96,0:05:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I will now return to the headquarters on Truk Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.86,0:05:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope to meet personally \Nwith the Combined Fleet Commander-in-Chief Koga {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mineichi_Koga}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.69,0:05:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell him how desperate things are on Rabaul. {lit: give him the sense of urgency of this Rabaul base}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.99,0:05:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take too long! {/It'll be too late.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.93,0:05:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time you'll reach Truk, \Nit'll be too late to do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy mobile task force with transports
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.41,0:05:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,are already being seen \Noff the coast of Bougainville and in the Coral Sea! {lit: appear frequently}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.71,0:05:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.70,0:05:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.58,0:05:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Scout to base. Scout to base. {no clue what's shiraeru here, kichi is clearly "base"; was "headquarters" in HA; shiru is "to know/let know" so maybe it's related}\NThis is Yame's plane of 305th Air Squadron.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.56,0:05:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy task force spotted:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.43,0:06:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,2 aircraft carriers, 2 cruisers, and 6 destroyers \Nmoving east-northeast in a circular battle formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.96,0:06:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Squad Commander, judging from the recent air raids \Nand the enemy fleet maneuvers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.72,0:06:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,their plan is to land either on Bougainville \Nor here on New Britain next.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.20,0:06:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's strike first! If we miss our chance to attack now, \Nwe'll come to regret it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.16,0:06:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yame managed to find the enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.94,0:06:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a task force with 2 aircraft carriers \Nsouth of Rendova Island. {I know for a fact this is a wrong and shoehorned translation but idk what's really anything before nanpou, the simplest explanation would've been that this rentouwatousei is one single landmark, but say it with me - there's no such landmark anywhere in the area; what I wrote would've been "rendobatou" and still doesn't account for sei part}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.75,0:06:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.52,0:06:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Headquarters! Headquarters! \NYame's plane speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.50,0:06:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Observing a separate formation. {/target}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.75,0:06:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll draw closer to confirm the composition \Nof the transport fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.54,0:06:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yame, turn back! Don't overdo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.78,0:06:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, the enemy really {\i1}is{\i0} landing somewhere today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.14,0:06:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gotta be either Bougainville or New Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.43,0:06:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If we let them pull that off, \Nthey'll have us on a silver plate! {lit: if that happens, it'll be the same as letting them put a dagger to our throats before our own eyes - uses japanese expression for "put a dirk to one's throat" but throat is replaced with hanasaki which can be both "tip of the nose" and "our own eyes"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.72,0:06:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it... If only we had more planes! {lit is "I want/need an airplane!" so maybe he means "I want them to give me clearance for takeoff"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.85,0:06:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do those mainland pricks \Nreally understand the situation? {/japan proper}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.48,0:06:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they perhaps think that we have \Nhundreds upon thousands of planes here in Rabaul?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.78,0:06:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, what was the Combined Fleet's \Nanswer to our proposal?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.76,0:06:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The strategy meeting is underway. {/is in discussion}\NStick to the designated strategy. {prescribed; designated; appointed; fixed - whatever that means}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.54,0:06:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If we delay for any longer, \NRabaul will repeat the fate of Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.47,0:07:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Headquarters! Headquarters! \NAbout 20 more enemy ships in a separate convoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.39,0:07:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Several Grummans ambushed me from behind! {(surprise) attack; assault; raid; charge}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.00,0:07:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yame? Yame! Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.44,0:07:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yame! Don't die!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.02,0:08:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lost contact!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.81,0:08:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Blazes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.80,0:08:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,To hell with it! {believing HA: I cannot stand it any longer.; no clue what he act. says}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.23,0:08:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Sasagawa! {beliving HA again}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.73,0:08:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sasagawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.13,0:08:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sasagawa, hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, please let me do it! \NI cannot let Yame die alone! {no clue what's mourechiga but dekimasen clearly means "cannot do ..."; was "I will save Yabe alone." in HA but that's baloney, they know for sure he's dead so it's gotta be some verb about dying: I can't let Yame die alone}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.66,0:08:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative! No unauthorized actions!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.16,0:08:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, I'm not afraid to die. {beliving HA, kinda hear "I don't ... life" there}\NIt's better than doing nothing. {no clue at all, was "I am ready to die at any time." in HA but I don't buy it; kinda hear "katte ni ... dekiteru" = "I can ... on my own/unauthorized"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.19,0:08:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sasagawa, I understand well how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.92,0:08:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all comrades who swore \Nto stick together even in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.19,0:08:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're also bound by the military discipline. {https://jisho.org/word/%E8%A6%8F%E5%BE%8B}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.82,0:08:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Unauthorized sorties are unacceptable. {until the order comes}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.57,0:08:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Sasagawa. \NJust dying is easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.99,0:09:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And we should at all times \Nbe prepared to ram the target, if needed. {suicide bombing (e.g. crashing one's plane into a target); self-destruction; blowing oneself up}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.78,0:09:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't mean risking our lives recklessly. {no clue whats word in the middle, kinda like inochi (life), kinda like gunjin (war hero (who died in battle)​); was "but don't die in vain." in HA and it makes sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.19,0:09:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yame knew full well he wasn't going to return home \Nwhen he took on this recon mission. {lit: accepted the role of searching for enemy on his own}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.91,0:09:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If we truly want to avenge him, \Nwe all have to value our own lives a little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.73,0:09:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be long till we get our chance \Nto die together. You hear, Sasagawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.93,0:09:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.07,0:09:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yame.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.53,0:09:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yame!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.37,0:09:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll definitely join you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.78,0:09:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Yonezawa of the press corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.12,0:09:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.23,0:09:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The Combined Fleet on Truk Island \Nseems rather reluctant to act upon the request from Rabaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.13,0:09:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.12,0:10:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,After securing Guadalcanal and the surrounding islands, \Nthe enemy will target Bougainville or New Britain next.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.41,0:10:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we really just going to give up on Rabaul, \Nlike we did with Guadalcanal?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.12,0:10:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a mere fighter pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.56,0:10:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't get a say in strategic decisions. {lit: strategy is being decided somewhere where our hands can't reach}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.23,0:10:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No, just think about it: if a strategy disregards completely \Nthe wishes of this foremost base, {/front line}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.27,0:10:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it means the Combined Fleet has lost their nerve \Never since the Midway debacle. {lit: became spineless; backboneless; timid; cowardly; weak-kneed}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.19,0:10:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened at Midway \Nis supposed to be a national secret. {/mainland}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.20,0:10:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the situation at Rabaul is passed on truthfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.69,0:10:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Such is the duty of the press corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.35,0:10:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get a chance, please tell the people on the mainland \Nto send in every plane they can. {unsure if he means the civilians or the high command}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.91,0:10:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, we're the Rabaul Air Corps \Nthat once was glorified in songs as invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.43,0:10:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Every fighter pilot longed to be enlisted in the Rabaul Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.59,0:10:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! Yamaguchi of the maintenance crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.33,0:10:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.23,0:10:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This frame took a beating during the daytime air raid. {/was shot}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.63,0:11:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think we can patch her up \Nif we replace the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.34,0:11:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, every single plane is precious for this base. {/Even a single aircraft more }
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.77,0:11:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope to make it into a fine Zero fighter \Nby tomorrow morning to please the crew.
