Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.20,0:11:21.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,00)\bord0\blur1\an3\move(800,-30,800,500,0,1600)\q2\t(2400,4800,\fs70)\c&H0C060E&} {\frz70} \h {Northern Mariana Archipelago} \h \N{\frz}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h Guam Island                             \h  \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                  Truk Island
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.05,0:11:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, at the Combined Fleet \NHeadquarters on Truk Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.16,0:11:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A formation of 2 aircraft carriers, 3 cruisers, \N4 destroyers, and 10 transport ships is heading north.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.19,0:11:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! Rabaul’s patrol aircraft spotted \Na separate fleet off the Shortland Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. What's the fleet's composition? {kazu is actually number so it's as though he's asking "So how many fleets are there"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.55,0:11:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Found an enemy task force: one aircraft carrier, \N2 cruisers, and 5 transports.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Also observing ships following after. {no clue what he means: please note, mitomu(prolly "seeing") succeeding/following targets }
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.37,0:11:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's either Bougainville or New Britain next.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.16,0:11:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! Please dispatch the planes and fleets \Nfrom Truk Island to Rabaul at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.00,0:11:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If we act now... \N{\i1}Only{\i0} if we act right now, will we make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.04,0:11:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.64,0:12:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our men on Rabaul are only waiting for your decisive order! \NTheir morale is still strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.98,0:12:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now's the time to mobilize \Nall of our fleet's resources and hit the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.85,0:12:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I also support the aviation adviser's point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.74,0:12:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit the enemy coming from the sea in the sea. \NThis is the iron rule of battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.85,0:12:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more, the Rabaul base \Nkeeps making increasing requests nigh daily. {not sure what's hirotsukuryouna}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.69,0:12:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispatch our air wings and fleets to Rabaul!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.77,0:12:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is aiming either for Bougainville or New Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.50,0:12:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We've no time to hesitate. \NIf we let them land unopposed now, we'll regret it later! {no clue waht he means: 上陸を図ってからでは悔いが残ります}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.52,0:12:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, this may present a chance for us \Nto avenge {the Battles of }Midway and the Solomon Islands!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.87,0:12:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, let's go for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.85,0:12:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The troops' morale is at a historical high.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.04,0:12:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's give the arrogant and disrespectful enemy \Na taste of our fighting spirit! {not really sure what he says but it's gotta be some colorful explanation of how they're gonna beat them - think "open a can of whoop-ass"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.72,0:12:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone call Vice Admiral Ozawa here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.92,0:12:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Commander-in-Chief of the Combined Fleet Koga
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.40,0:13:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,finally decided to respond to the desperate requests \Nfrom the Rabaul front line base.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.99,0:13:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The Third Fleet under the command of Vice Admiral Ozawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.71,0:13:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All the air wings of this fleet \Nwere sent to Rabaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.39,0:13:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Strategical decisions require quick and bold action.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.21,0:13:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In that sense, this decision \Ndid little to slow down the Americans. {unsure, maybe "was a little delayed by americans"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.45,0:13:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the early morning on the day \NOzawa's fleet arrived in Rabaul,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.73,0:13:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,using the bad weather from the previous days \Nto camouflage themselves, {/hide}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.20,0:13:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the American fleet of 18 transports and 9 escorts
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.45,0:13:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,initiated a surprise landing on Cape Torokina \Non the west coast of Bougainville Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.86,0:13:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened on November 1st, 1943.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.04,0:14:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Reinforcements arrived, \Nas promised by the Combined Fleet Commander. {no clue what's first word, added this commander; could actually be name of this pilot we see now}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.06,0:14:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.26,0:14:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,70 fighters from Zuikaku{ aircraft carrier} of the Ozawa's fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.05,0:14:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,70 Zero fighters from Shokaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.23,0:14:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,30 torpedo bombers from Zuiho.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.25,0:14:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Aside from those, a total of 180 more aircraft \Nshould arrive by the 3rd. {beliving HA, nc what's before hazuda}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.79,0:14:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.21,0:14:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you happy to see the reinforcements arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.73,0:14:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I am. But it's a shame they didn't arrive just a day earlier \Nto prevent the enemy from landing in Torokina.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.17,0:14:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So you've received a transfer to Rabaul?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.54,0:14:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to see you're doing well. {元気なようで何よりだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.04,0:14:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's pray that your luck in battle \Nnever runs out. And drink to it. {no clue what's bunkyokyuu, beliving HA: Now, pray for continued luck in the fortunes of war and make a toast.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.70,0:14:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something I need to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.93,0:14:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.16,0:15:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why didn't they dispatch Ozawa's fleet \Nbefore the enemy landed in Torokina?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.65,0:15:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.69,0:15:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hearing rumors of you distinguishing yourself as a pilot. \NI'm proud to have such a brilliant nephew.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.97,0:15:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.07,0:15:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, you can be intimidating too. {no clue what he really means: 時代というものは恐ろしい}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.92,0:15:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you aspired to be a lawyer before, \Nnow you're a military man to the marrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.81,0:15:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How many years does it take to become a full-fledged pilot these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.78,0:15:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Like the one such as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.77,0:15:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir. That'd be five years at least. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.33,0:15:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Five years, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.80,0:15:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't want our excellent pilots that take five years to train to lose their lives willy-nilly, would we?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.62,0:15:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The face of warfare is defined by airpower now. {/Starting now, the air power would mean everything in war}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.41,0:15:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think the conclusion to this war \Nwill be written here in Rabaul? {lit is "will end only in rabaul" w/e he means: お前はこの戦争がラバルだけで終わると思っているかね}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.60,0:15:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.74,0:15:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Making use of his numerical advantage, \Nthe enemy is now trying to mount a major counteroffensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.09,0:15:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At times like this, perhaps retreating to regroup \Nis preferable to just mindlessly attacking with all you've got. {/rebuild your formation}{not sure what he means, especially the soushiri wo ukete part: こんな時は総力を挙げて敵に対するより素知りを受けても後退し陣形を立て直すべきかもしれない}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.49,0:15:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so easy to relax with a relative, \NI unknowingly ended up just speaking my mind. {lit: between relatives, mind is at ease so I accidentally ended up saying some petty idle complaints; grumble}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.91,0:16:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's have a toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.15,0:16:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Sir. Let's raise it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.10,0:16:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot. Didn't you call me "uncle" just a moment ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.17,0:16:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We might never meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.26,0:16:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ensign Koga, what were you thinking, \Nvolunteering for such an assignment? {believing HA, not sure what he means by douka shitoru}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.61,0:16:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Rabaul is no longer the carefree paradise \Nlike in the songs they sing back on mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.16,0:16:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That was because the commander of the 305th \Nis my mentor Kamijo. {no clue what's tentou, no clue whatsoever what's konodzuyoi, HA: It is encouraging to know that the captain of the 305th is Senior Kamijo. - there's too few info on the web on 305th squadron to check if there was ever any commander by this name; whisper also has gibberish for this line: 店頭さん丸ごろ体調が上条先輩だとして頑張っていくことができる}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.31,0:16:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, Nida's plane speaking! {cant hear his name for sure }\NEnemy plane 30 degrees forward to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.45,0:16:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.46,0:16:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All pilots, enter the clouds dead ahead \Nand make a reverse sweep. {nc whats first word, could be koga tai (koga's formation)?; downhill rush; plunging down a precipice - probably means "make a dive"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.23,0:16:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Proceed! {no clue, "let's go" in HA, could be it, could be "fulfill it now" could be the pilot's response: roger!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.47,0:17:02.20,Song,,0,0,0,,Our silvery wings come together at the Southern Front {銀翼連ねて 南の前線}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.20,0:17:09.71,Song,,0,0,0,,The unshaken defense of our Sea Eagles {ゆるがぬ護りの 海鷲達が}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.71,0:17:17.41,Song,,0,0,0,,At the enemy's front line of human bullets {肉弾砕く 敵の主力}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.41,0:17:24.49,Song,,0,0,0,,Honor is with us. We are the Rabaul Naval Air Corps! {栄えある我等 ラバウル航空隊}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.35,0:18:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Rabaul Air Corps launched a promising \Nand fearless attack both on the sea and on land.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time, the results of that battle were announced by the Imperial Headquarters with great fanfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.15,0:18:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in the face of the immeasurable \Nquantitative advantage of the US Military,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.80,0:18:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Rabaul’s air power was being gradually depleted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.51,0:18:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The air battle off the Bougainville Island \Nwas still in full swing on November 13th, 1943,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when an unbelievable happening befell \Nthe airmen of the Rabaul Air Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.09,0:18:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The headquarters of the Ozawa's 3rd Fleet, \Nwhich came from Truk Island with reinforcements
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.28,0:18:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly made a 180 \Nand began pulling back towards Truk Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.81,0:18:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Same as before, it's just us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.25,0:18:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,An order has been issued \Nfor all the operable aircraft at Rabaul Base {/that can sortie }
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.67,0:19:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to immediately attack and destroy the enemy surface fleet \Nheading north through the seas west of Bougainville Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.01,0:19:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment, I have nothing new \Nto say to you before a sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.87,0:19:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But I pray sincerely that you fight bravely and reap success.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.07,0:19:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.97,0:19:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, please let me ride it with you. I beg you! {believing HA, nc what's the word before kudasai}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.09,0:19:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Cretin! You're still injured. Back off! {nc whats last word, sounds kinda like "out of my way"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.25,0:19:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But... Stick together even in death...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.64,0:19:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Eguchi, I'll be waiting for you at the Sanzu River crossing. {Sanzu River (Japanese Buddhist equivalent of the River Styx); River of Three Crossings​}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.79,0:19:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You come join me as soon as that arm heals up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.63,0:19:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.86,0:19:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.15,0:19:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.76,0:19:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.77,0:20:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.27,0:20:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, make sure to give Rabaul a look. \NIt might be your last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.64,0:20:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Flight Lieutenant Kamijo, my uncle asked me if I thought the conclusion to this war would be written in Rabaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.95,0:20:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Koga, you're concerned about the Ozawa's fleet \Nbeing pulled out of Rabaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.05,0:20:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I saw it coming. {predict; to guess; to forecast; to read (someone's thoughts); to see (e.g. into someone's heart); to divine}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.37,0:20:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Saw it, sir? {unsure, maybe it's still kamijo saying - "Yes, I did"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.75,0:20:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In his heart of hearts, your uncle, \Nthe Commander-in-Chief of the Combined Fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.28,0:20:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,knows that seizing this chance quickly \Nis even more important in defense than in attack. {lit: as a great commander, has to be quick to seize an opportunity even more in times of defense than in times of attack - kinda mouthful so was considering including Sun Tzu's "Invincibility lies in the defense; the possibility of victory in the attack."}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.67,0:20:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In that sense, it's us, the ones who have been constantly pressing for Ozawa's Fleet to be dispatched from Truk,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.88,0:20:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who are at fault for rocking the boat \Nand disconcerting your usually cool-headed uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.40,0:20:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.34,0:20:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard it, everyone? \NIt's now up to us to write a conclusion to this battle! {戦いはもう俺たちだけで終わりにさせようや - unsure, maybe he means "let the fight between us die out" but the next line suggest otherwise}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.60,0:20:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't mean you should be in a hurry to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.23,0:20:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Live to fight another day as best you can! {lit: as much as you can, try to survive and return home}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.10,0:20:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander! Enemy task force spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.54,0:20:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy planes, upper right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.62,0:21:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! Let's do it! {nc whats last word}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.21,0:21:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"We're engaging the enemy."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.41,0:21:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything after that? {/any later messages}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.61,0:21:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.80,0:21:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll live to fight another day! {/return home alive}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Flight Lieutenant Kamijo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.62,0:21:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.62,0:21:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.69,0:22:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.86,0:22:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Live to fight another day. \NYou must live to fight another day!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.43,0:22:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the spirit of the Rabaul Air Corps! {maybe add "Spirit of ... Air Corps" for more dramatic effect or replace with "carry on with the soul of Rabaul" since tamashi is soul/heart}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.98,0:23:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,On February 1st, 1944, the US Army made one big leap \Nand landed on the Marshall Islands. {(at) one bound}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.93,0:23:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,On February 17th, that same task force invaded Truk,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.30,0:23:08.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\frz299.6\b1\blur1\move(749.63,484.8,1714.12,298.8,2,2087)\c&H050108&}Marshall Archipelago
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.10,0:23:09.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H0A020C&\bord0\blur1\b1\frz356.3\move(-180,600,699.98,408,36,2021)}Truk Archipelago
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.83,0:23:11.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H0A020C&\bord0\blur1\b1\frz356.3\move(699.98,408,1206.69,1100,400,1894)}Truk Archipelago
Dialogue: 1,0:23:08.91,0:23:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,following it up with air raids on Tinian and Saipan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.33,0:23:13.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\q2\c&H0A020C&\bord0\blur1\b1\frz75.49\move(-142.24,-434,446.62,454,17,2000)}Mariana Archipelago \N{\frz-3} \h                                                                                   Saipan \N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                                                      Tinian \N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                    Guam
Dialogue: 1,0:23:12.93,0:23:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Rabaul was left far behind the front lines, \Nfully isolated and neutralized.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.75,0:23:18.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\q2\c&H0A020C&\bord0\blur1\b\pos(222.31,52)}Mariana Archipelago \NSaipan \NTinian \NGuam \N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                                                                                               Marshall Archipelago \N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                                    Truk Archipelago \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N \h                                                     Rabaul
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.45,0:23:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Amidst this all-consuming trend \Nof things going downhill everywhere, {　"Rolling down a hill" is an idiom used to describe how things deteriorate rapidly, like a spherical object rolling down a hill. - refers to how Japan was losing positions like a domino at the time}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.71,0:23:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't any kind of decision at all \Nseem ultimately futile and powerless?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.09,0:23:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's another one of those things \Nthat only heaven knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.26,0:24:08.05,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.67,0:24:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,July 1943.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.04,0:24:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army garrisons \Nthe Kiska Island with 5,600 soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.06,0:24:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet it's on the verge of being crushed \Nby the concentrated attack of the US Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.36,0:24:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Major General Kimura receives the order \Nto rescue the entire garrison.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.58,0:24:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll attempt a daring and fearless plan to hide in the fog \Nand sneak away from under the wary enemy's nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.80,0:24:39.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 16 \NEvacuation of Kiska {キスカ島撤退}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.71,0:24:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Witness the next week's decision: \NEvacuation of Kiska.
Comment: 0,0:24:43.11,0:24:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.17,0:24:49.00,Default,,0,0,50,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.00,0:24:52.93,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, keep your hopes sizzling{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.93,0:24:57.16,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.16,0:25:05.73,Default,,0,0,50,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.73,0:25:14.11,Default,,0,0,50,,With crimson blood flowing in our veins all the same{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
